Package com.jswiff.swfrecords.tags

Class Summary
DefineBits Defines a bitmap character with JPEG compression.
DefineBitsJPEG2 Defines a bitmap character with JPEG compression.
DefineBitsJPEG3 Defines a bitmap character with JPEG compression.
DefineBitsLossless Defines a lossless bitmap character that contains RGB data compressed with ZLIB.
DefineBitsLossless2 Defines a lossless bitmap character that contains RGB and alpha channel (transparency) data compressed with ZLIB.
DefineButton This tag defines a button character.
DefineButton2 This tag defines a button character.
DefineButtonCXform Specifies a color transform for a button defined with the DefineButton tag.
DefineButtonSound This tag determines the Flash Player to play sounds on a button's state transitions.
DefineEditText This tag defines a dynamic text field.
DefineFont This tag defines the shape outlines of each glyph used in a particular font.
DefineFont2 This tag is used to supply font information.
DefineFont3 This tag's structure is identical to DefineFont2.
DefineFontAlignment  
DefineFontInfo This tag maps a glyph font (defined with DefineFont) to a device font, providing a font name, style attributes (e.g. bold, italic) and a table of characters matching the glyph shape table contained in the corresponding DefineFont tag, thereby defining a one-to-one mapping between glyphs and characters.
DefineFontInfo2 Like DefineFontInfo, this tag also maps a glyph font (defined with DefineFont) to a device font, providing a font name, style attributes (e.g. bold, italic) and a table of characters matching the glyph shape table contained in the corresponding DefineFont tag, thereby defining a one-to-one mapping between glyphs and characters.
DefineMorphShape This tag is used to define the start and end states of a morph sequence.
DefineMorphShape2 DOCUMENT ME!
DefineShape This tag defines a shape, assigning it a character ID.
DefineShape2 This tag is used to define shapes, just like DefineShape.
DefineShape3 This tag is used to define shapes, just like DefineShape and DefineShape2.
DefineShape4 Used to define shapes, similar to DefineShape, DefineShape2 and DefineShape3.
DefineSound This tag defines an event sound.
DefineSprite This tag defines a sprite character (i.e. a movie inside the main SWF movie).
DefineText This tag defines a block of static text.
DefineText2 This tag defines a block of static text, just like DefineText.
DefineVideoStream This tag defines the format of a streaming video data contained in subsequent VideoFrame tags.
DefinitionTag Base class for definition tags, which define new characters.
DoAction This tag instructs Flash Player to execute a series of actions when encountering the next ShowFrame tag, after all drawing for the current frame has completed.
DoInitAction This tag contains a series of initialization actions for a particular sprite.
EnableDebugger This tag enables debugging within the Macromedia Flash authoring tool.
EnableDebugger2 This tag enables debugging within the Macromedia Flash authoring tool.
ExportAssets This tag makes one or more defined characters available for import by other SWF files.
ExportAssets.ExportMapping Defines an (immutable) export mapping for a character to be exported, containing its ID and its export name.
FileAttributes This tag is used as of SWF 8 to define SWF properties like access mode and the presence of metadata.
FlashTypeSettings  
FrameLabel This tag assigns a certain name to the current frame.
FreeCharacter This tag removes a character with a given ID, thereby freeing memory from Flash Player.
ImportAssets This tag imports one or more characters from an SWF file.
ImportAssets.ImportMapping Defines an (immutable) import mapping for a character, containing its export name and the ID the character instance gets after import.
ImportAssets2 TODO: Comments
JPEGTables This tag contains the JPEG encoding table (the Tables/Misc segment) for all JPEG images defined in the SWF file with the DefineBits tag.
MalformedTag This tag is used as container for malformed tag data which could not be interpreted.
Metadata Contains XML metadata in Dublin Core RDF format.
PlaceObject This tag adds a character instance to the display list.
PlaceObject2 With this tag, an instance of a character can be added to the display list.
PlaceObject3 TODO: Comments
Protect This tag is used to advise SWF editors to restrict edition capabilities for the current SWF ducument.
RemoveObject The RemoveObject tag removes the instance of a particular character at the specified depth from the display list.
RemoveObject2 The RemoveObject2 tag removes the character instance at the specified depth from the display list.
Scale9Grid  
ScriptLimits This tag is used to override the default values for maximum recursion depth (i.e. how often a function can call itself) and timeout regarding the execution of actions.
SetBackgroundColor This tag contains the background color of the SWF.
SetTabIndex This tag is used to set the tab order index of character instances.
ShowFrame This tag instructs Flash Player to display all characters added (either with PlaceObject or PlaceObject2) to the display list.
SoundStreamBlock This tag contains raw streaming sound data.
SoundStreamHead This tag is used to define the format of streaming sound data (contained in SoundStreamBlock tags).
SoundStreamHead2 This tag is used to define the format of streaming sound data (contained in SoundStreamBlock tags).
StartSound This tag instructs the Flash Player to play a sound previously defined with the DefineSound tag.
Tag Base class for SWF tags.
TagConstants This class contains constants regarding SWF tags.
TagHeader This class represents a SWF tag header.
TagReader This class contains methods used for parsing tag headers and tags.
TagWriter This class contains methods used for writing tag headers and tags.
UnknownTag This class implements a container for tag data which cannot be interpreted because the tag type is unknown (e.g. for new Flash versions).
VideoFrame This tag provides a single frame of streaming video data.
